Final Readiness Framework (Use This)

👉 “Can our platform support a new line of business with minimal change?”

The 5 Pillars:
Data Model
Processing / Workflow
Integration
Security & Compliance
Monitoring, Alerts & Reconciliation
🧩 1. Data Model Readiness
Question	Why it matters	Signal
Can current group / division / member hierarchy support this LOB?	Core structure	Schema vs reuse
Are new attributes needed (benefits, billing, product)?	Extensibility	Minor vs major change
Can onboarding be config-driven?	Speed	Config = scalable
⚙️ 2. Processing & Workflow Readiness
Question	Why it matters	Signal
Does this follow existing transaction types (add/change/term/renew)?	Flow reuse	Reuse vs redesign
Will it be systematic or manual heavy?	Operational complexity	Manual = risk
Do current services support this logic?	Service reuse	Tweaks vs rebuild
🔗 3. Integration & Downstream Readiness
Question	Why it matters	Signal
Can downstream systems consume existing event format?	Integration stability	Mapping vs redesign
Are new event types or statuses needed?	Tracking impact	Schema evolution
Does this affect reconciliation logic?	Audit impact	Needs updates
🔐 4. Security & Compliance Readiness

👉 Keep this focused and practical, not theoretical.

Question	Why it matters	Signal
Does this LOB introduce new sensitive data types (PHI, PII variations)?	Compliance risk	Encryption / masking updates
Are current access controls (role-based) sufficient?	Data protection	New roles or scopes needed
Do audit logs capture who changed what and when for this flow?	Regulatory requirement	Logging gaps
Does data flow across new systems or boundaries?	Risk surface	Needs security review

💡 Simple takeaway:
“If data sensitivity or access patterns change, security must evolve with it.”

📡 5. Monitoring, Alerts & Reconciliation

👉 This is where most systems fail — and where you’ll stand out.

A. Monitoring
Question	Why it matters	Signal
Can we track transaction progress end-to-end?	Visibility	Event tracking completeness
Do we know where a transaction is stuck?	Debugging	Gap detection needed
B. Alerts
Question	Why it matters	Signal
Do we have alerts for failures, delays, or missing steps?	SLA protection	Needs alert rules
Can we differentiate pending vs failed vs stuck?	Operational clarity	CP status usage
C. Reconciliation
Question	Why it matters	Signal
Do we have control totals (group, division, member)?	Completeness check	Works for systematic
How do we reconcile manual transactions?	Known gap	Needs status-based tracking
Can we match source → EnrollPoint → downstream using Event ID?	Core audit capability	Correlation strength

💡 Simple takeaway:
“If we cannot track, alert, and reconcile — we don’t truly support the business.”

🧠 Executive Summary (what YOU say)

👉
“To evaluate a new line of business, we’re focusing on five things:

Can our data model represent it?
Can our workflows process it?
Can downstream systems consume it?
Is it secure and compliant?
And can we monitor and reconcile it end-to-end?”

👉
“If we’re strong across these five, we can onboard with minimal effort and reuse most of the platform.”
